"{\"uid\": \"c-mw.net-paris-olympics-sees-increases-in-air-arrivals-and-hotel-occupancy\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A tourism report released for the Paris Olympics shows that international air arrivals are expected to rise 7.9% on 2023.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"North America is particularly responsible with an expected 16.1% increase (108,000 arrivals), with European arrivals projected to rise 4.3% (to 76,000).\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hotel occupancy rates are up across all d\\u00e9partements of the inner suburbs.\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In inner Paris, hotel occupancy is up 10.1% on 2023, with a particularly sharp rise in the top end of the market (16.5%).\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998324256, \"rank\": 1.6762643190510651e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The arrondissements of Paris most visited by foreign tourists between 23 July and 6 August are:  Of total visitors, 44.6% were \\u00cele-de-France residents, 27.7% were day-trippers and another 27.7% were tourists.\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998324256, \"rank\": 1.6762643190510651e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\", \"score\": 0.9999571055152909, \"rank\": 4.2884246434920753e-05, \"text\": \"\\u00cele-de-France\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top three foreign markets for international tourists were the United States (230,000), Germany (130,000) and the UK (115,000).\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992046469, \"rank\": 6.113586309824786e-10, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9291085615756891, \"rank\": 0.07629606548435271, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 801, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9822962047990993, \"rank\": 0.017929897841024094, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three international long-haul markets that saw significant growth were Brazil (107,000), China (82,000) and Japan (47,000).\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999965601537087, \"rank\": 1.7419102385201884e-06, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.6815092087057569, \"rank\": 0.4671104890952995, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://